blog.name: alexandro-lima
blog.title: Alexandro Lima - Ilustrador
blog.description: Olá, bem vindo ao meu blog! Sou um ilustrador/arte finalista publicitário com larga experiência de mercado. Considero como seus “mestres inspiradores” Will Eisner, Jack Kirby, John Buscema e Canini. Sou um apreciador de quadrinhos, utilizo muito desta que é considerada a nona arte como fonte de referência para muitos de seus trabalhos.Mesclo trabalho à mão com vetorização e colorização digital em meus trabalhos. Realizo ilustrações, caricaturas, logotipos e pinturas. Este blog tem o objetivo de mostrar o que mais atual ando produzindo. Divulgue e opine!

Capitão  America - Reb Brown

Série de dois telefilmes para TV em 1979 feito para televisão estrelado por Reb Brown.

Steve...
caption:
Capitão America - Reb Brown

Série de dois telefilmes para TV em 1979 feito para televisão estrelado por Reb Brown.

Steve Rogers ( Reb Brown ) é um homem contemporâneo cujo pai era um agente do governo dos anos 40. A atitude muito patriótica do pai de Steve lhe valeu o apelido de “Capitão América”. Seu pai foi posteriormente assassinado. Rogers, um ex-fuzileiro agora ganhando a vida como artista e viajando pelo interior em uma van, é inspirado pela história de seu pai para esboçar um super-herói. 

Depois de receber ferimentos potencialmente fatais em uma tentativa em sua vida destinada a parecer um acidente, ele recebe uma substância química experimental chamada fórmula FLAG; FLAG é um acrônimo para “Full Latent Ability Gain”, uma espécie de “super-esteróide”. (O pai de Rogers havia desenvolvido o soro FLAG de suas próprias glândulas.)

A fórmula não apenas salva sua vida, mas aumenta sua força e reflexos. Essas novas habilidades inspiram o Dr. Simon Mills, o pesquisador bioquímico e funcionário de inteligência por trás da FLAG que já foi amigo do pai de Steve, para recrutar Steve e dar a ele uma fantasia baseada em seu desenho. Como Capitão América, a van de Steve é ​​reconfigurada para que possa lançar uma motocicleta de alta tecnologia.

summary: Okay but listen. Imagine that (because Tony) The Avengers Tower if fully equipped with musical instruments, but the others don't...
body:
Okay but listen. Imagine that (because Tony) The Avengers Tower if fully equipped with musical instruments, but the others don’t know. Once the avengers were discussing music taste and Natasha says that she could play a couple of songs on guitar (knowing Nat, she’s probably tipsy). It ends up being a bet and before they know it, boom, there’s a guitar in her hands. After a shredding solo, Bruce asks Tony if he has a drum kit nearby. On cue, JARVIS rolls one out. Bruce goes all like “I’m sorry, this will be terrible but I’m gonna try”. He then starts playing slowly, then slowly accelerates. After a minute, he is absolutely lost in the moment, playing his heart out. Everyone is enjoying the time, until Cap notices that Banner’s veins are turning green. Everyone panics as Bruce transforms into the Hulk. But instead of destroying everything, the green creature continues playing this intense, complicated song. After a while, the song gets quieter, just the sounds of cymbals softly rippling through the air. The Hulk slowly transforms back. Banner looks exhausted, but continues playing nonetheless. The song intensifies once more, until it stops.

Natasha runs up and helps him to the sofa. He is asleep before his head touches the pillow. When he wakes up, he sees a concerned assassin looking at him, worry in her eye. She asks him why he did it, knowing what would happen. He tells her that the other guy was pressing him because he was kept in for too long and music is the way for him to release him without causing chaos. It’s a mutual agreement, he says, but asks her not to tell the others. Ever since, Stark won’t stop calling Bruce “Avenger Sevenfold.”

She asks him why he did it, knowing what would happen. He tells her that the other guy was pressing him because he was kept in for too long and music is the way for him to release him without causing chaos. It’s a mutual agreement, he says, but asks her not to tell the others. Ever since, Stark won’t stop calling Bruce “Avenger Sevenfold.”
trail.content:
Okay but listen. Imagine that (because Tony) The Avengers Tower if fully equipped with musical instruments, but the others don’t know. Once the avengers were discussing music taste and Natasha says that she could play a couple of songs on guitar (knowing Nat, she’s probably tipsy). It ends up being a bet and before they know it, boom, there’s a guitar in her hands. After a shredding solo, Bruce asks Tony if he has a drum kit nearby. On cue, JARVIS rolls one out. Bruce goes all like “I’m sorry, this will be terrible but I’m gonna try”. He then starts playing slowly, then slowly accelerates. After a minute, he is absolutely lost in the moment, playing his heart out. Everyone is enjoying the time, until Cap notices that Banner’s veins are turning green. Everyone panics as Bruce transforms into the Hulk. But instead of destroying everything, the green creature continues playing this intense, complicated song. After a while, the song gets quieter, just the sounds of cymbals softly rippling through the air. The Hulk slowly transforms back. Banner looks exhausted, but continues playing nonetheless. The song intensifies once more, until it stops.

Natasha runs up and helps him to the sofa. He is asleep before his head touches the pillow. When he wakes up, he sees a concerned assassin looking at him, worry in her eye. She asks him why he did it, knowing what would happen. He tells her that the other guy was pressing him because he was kept in for too long and music is the way for him to release him without causing chaos. It’s a mutual agreement, he says, but asks her not to tell the others. Ever since, Stark won’t stop calling Bruce “Avenger Sevenfold.”
